These macros exist to execute instructions for jobs, including particle identity, energy, and number of desired events.

To run a macro that automates bash commands or GUI commands:
`./executable /filepath_name/macro.mac`

One can also just copy and paste the contents of a macro into an executable .sh file and submit a job using that automated executable file.  For example, using the `nohup` job submission command and printing the outputs to a log file:
`nohup ./executable_script.sh > name_of_log_file.log 2>&1 &`

To check on status and get job ID number: `ps -ef | grep executable_script.sh`
To see most recent activity in the job: `tail -f name_of_log_file.log`
